stylometry: The tradeoff between price and demand is that when price increases, demand decreases. This is also considered elasticity of demand. When we are setting the price of a product or service, we need to find the price point where we will make the most profit. We must be careful when trying to make higher profit margins, that the demand decreases below a level where the margin will be beneficial to the company. In order to set the price of a product, first we find the price elasticity of demand (PED). When this number (always listed in absolute value) is less then one, price is realitively inelastic, meaning that a change in price has very little effect on demand. The opposite is true when the number is greater then one, where price has a high effect on demand. When the PED is equal to one, that is the best price point for the product.
